paragraphs.text:
%md
BDC ships with two installs of Python: "system" and "user"

+ System Python: 2.6.6. This is the version that is shipped and standard with the version of Oracle Linux currently used in BDC.  This version is left unchanged to not disrupt other operating system processes which depend on it.
+ User Python : 2.7.x. BDC configures this version for PySpark and Zeppelin.  It is located at /u01/bdcsce/usr/local/bin/python
    
It should be noted that the default PATH for linux users will pickup the system python.

msg.data:
BDC ships with two installs of Python: “system” and “user”

  • System Python: 2.6.6. This is the version that is shipped and standard with the version of Oracle Linux currently used in BDC. This version is left unchanged to not disrupt other operating system processes which depend on it.
  • User Python : 2.7.x. BDC configures this version for PySpark and Zeppelin. It is located at /u01/bdcsce/usr/local/bin/python

It should be noted that the default PATH for linux users will pickup the system python.

paragraphs.text:
%sh
echo "System python versions."
python -V
pip -V

sleep 8
# use a sleep so that output does not appear out of order
echo ".."
echo ".."

echo "User python versions."
/u01/bdcsce/usr/local/bin/python -V
/u01/bdcsce/usr/local/bin/pip -V
